The new super-powerful Samsung Galaxy Note 9 is now available for pre-order from Technomobi, Standout features of the device include a 6.4-inch AMOLED display with a resolution of 2,960 x 1,440, a powerful all-day 4,000mAh battery, and a new-and-improved Bluetooth stylus. It also features an intelligent dual-sensor camera system, which make it virtually impossible to take a bad shot, 128GB of built-in storage, and microSD support for a 512GB card. The Galaxy Note 9 is available in three colours in South Africa – Midnight Black, Metallic Copper, and Ocean Blue – while the Lavender Purple variant will be available shortly after the device’s arrival in the country. The online retailer stated that pre-orders for the device start at R18,999, and will ship from 7 September. To pre-order, or for more information, visit the Technomobi website. Specifications for the Samsung Galaxy Note 9 are listed in the table below.     This article was published in partnership with Technomobi.